2. How to use TNS_NAMES in jdbc urls
   2.1. Add jvm commandline option '-Doracle.net.tns_admin'. Value of this property should point to the directory containing 'tnsnames.ora' file e.g. -Doracle.net.tns_admin=/path/to/tnsadmin/
   2.2 Change value of jdbc.url property to 'jdbc:oracle:thin:@TNS_NAME
here TNS_NAME is name of the entry in tns file pointing to your DB cluster
  

